 Choices:

evidence: Postmaster General Louis DeJoy backed down on proposed changes to the US Postal Service, which included retail hour changes and removal of blue mail collection boxes, until after the November presidential election. input_wo_instruction_answer_w_choices:

 Choices: 
 0:Engaging in passive-aggressive banter
 1:Stalling to keep something from happening
 2:Talking over another person
 3:Concentrating on minor details
choices1: Stalling to keep something from happening
evidence: Pettifogging means “worrying too much about details that are minor or not important." Roberts used the word to refer to a complaint made during a 1905 trial. He was trying to say that people used to hold others to a higher standard of trial conduct, and so should the participants of the impeachment trial.
